# ── Go ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Compiled binary — name matches the module name in go.mod
goblog
goblog.exe

# Build artifacts
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib
*.test
*.out

# Go workspace file (Go 1.18+)
go.work
go.work.sum

# ── Database ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SQLite database — recreated automatically on first run via initDB()
*.db
*.db-shm
*.db-wal
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3

# ── Uploads ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# User-uploaded cover images — not part of source code
static/uploads/

# ── Tailwind / Node ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Node modules — restored with `npm install`
tailwind/node_modules/

# Compiled CSS is generated by the Tailwind CLI watcher.
# Two valid schools of thought:
#   - Commit it so the app works on deploy without a build step (recommended for simplicity)
#   - Ignore it and add a build step to your CI/CD pipeline
# We commit it here for simplicity. Comment out the line below if you prefer not to.
# static/css/tailwind.css

# ── Environment & Secrets ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# If you later add a .env file for secrets (DB URL, secret key, etc.)
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# ── Editor & OS ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# VS Code
.vscode/
*.code-workspace

# JetBrains (GoLand)
.idea/
*.iml

# macOS
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride

